## Overarching Technical Intent
1. Shadows should be both accurate and fast.
2. GPU does per-pixel work; CPU should not be the default shadow raster/sampling bottleneck.
3. Backend parity should come from shared contract semantics and mirrored backend capability, not lowest-common-denominator quality.
4. Keep clean separation:
   - engine owns contracts/lifecycle,
   - backends own backend specifics,
   - game consumes engine abstractions only.

